---
title: Penne with a Kick in a Pancetta Tomato Arrabbiata Sauce
description: Maybe it’s just us, but pasta sauce from a jar makes us mad. Its flavors are dull compared to what you can make with a little effort at home. Whoever invented arrabbiata must have had us in mind: the name literally comes from the Italian word for angry. Made with blushing red tomatoes and accented with chili pepper heat, this pasta sauce is lively and bright. It comes together in a cinch, too!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/penne-with-a-kick-31f1c741.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/penne-with-a-kick-6666d5a6.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/penne-with-a-kick-597b428351d3f11af66a80b2
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 730 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Core, seed, and dice @Roma tomato{1}(cored, seeded, and diced). Mince @chili pepper{1}(minced).

Heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add half the @pancetta{2%oz} from package (we sent more) and cook, tossing occasionally, until slightly crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Toss in onion and as much chili as you like. Cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add garlic and toss until fragrant, about ~{1%minute} longer. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, reserving ½ cup pasta cooking water.

Add Roma tomato, @diced tomatoes{1%can}, and @sugar{1%tsp} to pan. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add penne and @spinach{5%oz} to sauce and toss until spinach is wilted. Stir in as much pasta cooking water as is needed to loosen sauce and give it a loose consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between plates. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and serve.